# File Length Limit: 200 Lines

Any file exceeding 200 lines MUST be split into multiple files.

## How to Split

1. Identify logical sections (each section gets its own file)
2. Name split files with a shared prefix and section suffix
3. Each file must start with a clear title heading

## Documentation Example

```
# Too long:
docs/PRD.md  (450 lines)

# Split into:
docs/PRD-overview.md       (~120 lines) - vision, goals, personas
docs/PRD-requirements.md   (~150 lines) - functional + non-functional
docs/PRD-epics.md          (~180 lines) - epic breakdown
```

## Source Code Example

```
# Too long:
src/core/types.ts  (300 lines)

# Split into:
src/core/types/storage.ts    - IStorageAdapter, StorageError
src/core/types/network.ts    - INetworkAdapter, NetworkError
src/core/types/sync.ts       - SyncStatus, SyncProgress, SyncExecutor
src/core/types/index.ts      - re-exports all
```

## Rules

- Check line count BEFORE writing. If projected > 200, plan the split first.
- Each split file must be self-contained with its own imports.
- Use a barrel `index.ts` or a table-of-contents README to link split files.
